Entries.default: "Did you see those awful verses by the kitchen?"
"Peyro cheats, I'm telling you."
"I get along fine with him. He's straightforward to me."
"They weren't that bad..."
"It's impossible to cheat at hazatōha."
"One minute he's all charm, then he cuts me down with a word."
"Rhyming 'hazanui' with 'kablooey'?"
"I can't think of anything else that goes with 'hazanui.'"
"Me neither. That's why I leave epics to the lore college."
"Criticism is easier than creation."
"He acts like he's going to do one thing, then he does something else!"
"That's called strategy. And don't you work for Atsura?"
"Are we talking about the same Atsura?"
"My cousin at Sayuka said her work's finally continuing. Won't say what it is."
"You haven't figured it out? I thought it was obvious."
"You tell me if you're so smart."
"I can't. It's a big secret."
"Uh huh. Someone's afraid of being wrong."
"I want to crew on the Blade of Tākowa. Think the Watcher'd hire me?"
"You'd fill the damn thing with so much hot air it'd never dive."
"I thought Iverra's developments were supposed to help with that."
"You know what? Forget it."
"I heard the hazanui's sending for the Gunhawks."
"I saw one shoot once. Hit a lurch shark in the eye from two hundred feet away."
